<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/381a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>, Temporarily in Useppa, Florida</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-25">February 25, 1935</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Forthomme impressed upon me today importance of signing Belgian
                                agreement before executive authority to sign expires on February
                                28th. After this date powers revert to Parliament. He fears debates
                                in Parliament and unfavorable reaction resulting possibly in defeat
                                of agreement owing to terms as modified and slight concessions to
                                Belgium.</p>
                            <p>Shall call you on telephone 10 o’clock tomorrow. Have today sent text
                                of agreement to President.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>